#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:58
msgid ""
"Normalized percentage (0% to 100%) of the remaining space capacity. If "
"Available Spare is lower than Available Space Threshold, the drive is "
"considered to be in a critical state."
msgstr ""
"通常的剩余空间容量的百分比（0%至100%）。如果可用剩余空间低于可用空间阈值，则"
"认为该驱动器处于临界状态。"

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:62
msgid ""
"Normalized percentage (0% to 100%). If the Available Spare is lower than "
"this threshold, the drive is considered to be in a critical state."
msgstr ""
"常用的百分比（0%至100%）。如果可用空间低于此阈值，则认为驱动器处于临界状态。"

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:65
msgid ""
"Vendor-specific estimate of the percentage of device life based on the "
"actual device usage and the manufacturer's prediction of the device life. A "
"value of 100 indicates that the estimated endurance of the device has been "
"consumed, but may not indicate a device failure. This value is allowed to "
"exceed 100. Percentage values greater than 254 are be represented as 255. "
"This value is updated once per power-on hour (when the controller is not in "
"a sleep state)."
msgstr ""
"基于实际设备使用情况和制造商对设备寿命的预测，供应商对设备寿命百分比的具体估"
"计。值100表示设备的估计耐用性已耗尽，但可能并不表示设备故障。该值允许超过"
"100。大于254的百分比值将表示为255。该值在每次开机一小时（当控制器未处于睡眠状"
"态时）更新一次。"

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:71
msgid ""
"The number of 512-byte data units the host has read from the controller. "
"This value does not include metadata. The value is reported in thousands "
"(i.e. a value of 1 corresponds to 1000 units of 512 bytes read) and is "
"rounded up. When the LBA size is a value other than 512 bytes, the "
"controller converts the amount of data read to 512-byte units."
msgstr ""
"主机从控制器读取的512字节数据单元的数量。此值不包括元数据。该值以千为单位报告"
"（即，值1对应读取1000个512字节单元），并向上取整。当LBA大小不是512字节时，控"
"制器会将读取的数据量转换为512字节单元。"

#: src/applib/storage_property_descr_nvme_attribute.cpp:77
msgid ""
"The number of 512-byte data units the host has written to the controller. "
"This value does not include metadata. The value is reported in thousands "
"(i.e. a value of 1 corresponds to 1000 units of 512 bytes read) and is "
"rounded up."
